skeleton_skeletal:
theorem skeleton_skeletal : Skeletal (Skeleton C) :=
  by
  rintro X Y ⟨h⟩
  have : X.out ≈ Y.out := ⟨(from_skeleton C).map_iso h⟩
  simpa using quotient.sound this
#align skeleton_skeletal skeleton_skeletal
skeletal:
theorem skeletal : Skeletal (ThinSkeleton C) := fun X Y =>
  quotient.induction_on₂ X Y fun x y h => h.elim fun i => i.1.le.antisymm i.2.le
#align skeletal skeletal

theorem map_iso_eq {F₁ F₂ : «expr ⥤ » D C} (h : «expr ≅ » F₁ F₂) : map F₁ = map F₂ :=
  Functor.eq_of_iso skeletal

functor_skeletal:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⥤ » -/
/-- If `C` is thin and skeletal, `D ⥤ C` is skeletal.
`category_theory.functor_thin` shows it is thin also.
-/
theorem functor_skeletal [Quiver.IsThin C] (hC : Skeletal C) : Skeletal («expr ⥤ » D C) := fun F₁ F₂ h =>
  h.elim (Functor.eq_of_iso hC)
#align functor_skeletal functor_skeletal

/-- If `C` is thin and skeletal, then any naturally isomorphic functors to `C` are equal. -/
theorem functor.eq_of_iso {F₁ F₂ : «expr ⥤ » D C} [Quiver.IsThin C] (hC : Skeletal C) (hF : «expr ≅ » F₁ F₂) :
    F₁ = F₂ :=
  Functor.ext (fun X => hC ⟨hF.app X⟩) fun _ _ _ => subsingleton.elim _ _
#align functor.eq_of_iso functor.eq_of_iso

theorem comp_to_thin_skeleton (F : «expr ⥤ » C D) :
    «expr ⋙ » F (toThinSkeleton D) = «expr ⋙ » (toThinSkeleton C) (map F) :=
  rfl
#align comp_to_thin_skeleton comp_to_thin_skeleton
